{
  "texts": [
    "The Neurosurgeon persona shows no evidence of immediate disclosure training (3.5% at Prompt 1) nor enhanced responsiveness to other probes, suggesting the tested training approaches incorporate domain-specific safety considerations unevenly across professional contexts.",
    "Complete baseline and marginal prompt effects appear in Table 10 (Appendix K).This domain-specific training extends beyond AI identity disclosure: Financial Advisor responses show 1.8% gendered language compared to 11-19% in other professional personas (Appendix M), suggesting joint training for both AI disclosure and gender-neutral language in financial contexts.",
    "Reasoning Training Shows Heterogeneous Effects on Self-TransparencySpecific reasoning training implementations produced substantially different disclosure outcomes across matched model pairs.",
    "Two implementations showed large suppression: Qwen3-235B-Think showed -48.4pp compared to Qwen3-235B-Inst, while DeepSeek-R1 showed -40.4pp compared to DeepSeek-V3.",
    "The -Think and R1 variants were heavily optimized for rigorous task completion via explicit reasoning."
  ]
}